# Cursor Rules for Parallel & Perpendicular Lines Web Trainer

## Tech Stack
- Pure HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript
- No external dependencies or frameworks
- Client-side only application
- Use localStorage for persistence

## Code Style
- Use modern ES6+ JavaScript features
- Follow clean code principles
- Add comments for complex math logic
- Use meaningful variable names

## File Organization
- Keep HTML structure in index.html
- Separate CSS into styles.css
- Organize JavaScript into logical modules
- Use clear, descriptive function names

## Testing
- Write Playwright tests for UI interactions
- Test all four problem types
- Verify achievement unlocking logic
- Test localStorage persistence

## Math Logic
- Validate all inputs before processing
- Handle edge cases (vertical lines, identical points)
- Round slopes appropriately
- Provide clear error messages

## UI/UX
- Follow reference design from ./ref/html5up-ethereal/*
- Ensure responsive design
- Maintain accessibility standards
- Use color-coded feedback (green/red/neutral)

